The Hokkoku Bank, Ltd. (8363) : Company Profile and SWOT Analysis, Timetric

February 2016
28 pages
Timetric
        

Report ID: 3638369



Summary
Table of contents
Search Inside


SynopsisTimetric's "The Hokkoku Bank, Ltd. (8363) : Company Profile and SWOT Analysis" contains in depth information and data about the company and its operations. The profile contains a company overview, key facts, major products and services, SWOT analysis, business description, company history, financial analysis, key employees, company locations and subsidiaries as well as competitive benchmarking data.SummaryThis report is a crucial resource for industry executives and anyone looking to access key information about "The Hokkoku Bank, Ltd."The report utilizes a wide range of primary and secondary sources, which are analyzed and presented in a consistent and easily accessible format. Timetric strictly follows a standardized research methodology to ensure high levels of data quality and these characteristics guarantee a unique report.Scope - Examines and identifies key information and issues about "The Hokkoku Bank, Ltd." for business intelligence requirements. - Studies and presents the company's strengths, weaknesses, opportunities (growth potential) and threats (competition). Strategic and operational business information is objectively reported. - Provides data on company financial performance and competitive benchmarking. - The profile also contains information on business operations, company history, major products and services, key employees, and locations and subsidiaries.Reasons To Buy - Quickly enhance your understanding of "The Hokkoku Bank, Ltd." - Gain insight into the marketplace and a better understanding of internal and external factors which could impact the industry. - Increase business/sales activities by understanding your competitors’ businesses better. - Recognize potential partnerships and suppliers.Key HighlightsThe Hokkoku Bank Ltd. (Hokkoku Bank) is a regional bank. The bank offers a range of banking products and services to individuals, corporate and SME clients. The portfolio of products offered by the bank includes time deposit accounts, foreign currency accounts, negotiable certificate of deposit, savings accounts, current accounts, cash cards, debit cards and credit cards. The bank also offers lease hold mortgages, apartment loans, home improvement loans, car loans, education loans, unsecured mortgages, large free loans, individual annuity insurance, term insurance, medical insurance, net insurance, oversea travel insurance and cancer insurance. Its service offering includes branch banking, fund management, credit guarantee, foreign currency services, safe deposit box, online banking, business solution map services, overseas banking support services, SME banking and advisory services related to merger and acquisition. The bank sells and distributes its products and services through network of branches and loan centers in Japan and representative offices located in Shanghai and Singapore. Hokkoku Bank is headquartered in Kanazawa Japan.
	

